description: I learned this as Western Sycamore, but it looks like the Arizona has been split from the California -- or maybe it's only the Calif. that's called Western.  At any rate, looks very similar to the ones I remember from Calif.; and distinctly different from the Eastern species (American Sycamore), which typically grows from a single, straight trunk & has darker, peely bark all the way up, not just around the base.
